to say smart things while I'm

00:08:32.990 --> 00:08:34.700
distracted cooking.

00:08:34.700 --> 00:08:35.241
Hi, Aralyn.

00:08:35.241 --> 00:08:36.199
ARALYN BEAUMONT: Hello.

00:08:36.199 --> 00:08:37.365
CHRIS YING: Welcome, Aralyn.

00:08:39.600 --> 00:08:41.012
How's it going, man?

00:08:41.012 --> 00:08:43.220
You're among the people who
have made sausage before.

00:08:43.220 --> 00:08:44.240
BRANDON CHALK: I am.

00:08:44.240 --> 00:08:44.963
CHRIS YING: OK.

00:08:44.963 --> 00:08:46.070
BRANDON CHALK: Not
chorizo, though.

00:08:46.070 --> 00:08:46.570
CHRIS YING: Not chorizo.

00:08:46.570 --> 00:08:48.315
BRANDON CHALK: But I think that
was my first recipe in the book

00:08:48.315 --> 00:08:49.050
