00:08:49.050 --> 00:08:49.340
CHRIS YING: All right.

00:08:49.340 --> 00:08:50.980
We're going to do it right here.

00:08:50.980 --> 00:08:56.571
Chorizo starts here.

00:08:56.571 --> 00:08:58.610
You know, a lot of people
are kind of turned off

00:08:58.610 --> 00:08:59.690
by the idea of making
sausage, because there's

00:08:59.690 --> 00:09:00.740
all this equipment involved.

00:09:00.740 --> 00:09:02.531
You've got to buy a
grinder, and a stuffer,

00:09:02.531 --> 00:09:03.860
and all this kind of stuff.

00:09:03.860 --> 00:09:06.910
But there's also just
loose, uncased sausage

00:09:06.910 --> 00:09:10.270
which most choirzo, when you
buy it from a Mexican grocery--

00:09:10.270 --> 00:09:14.130
it comes in a big bulk, then
you buy it by the pound.

00:09:14.130 --> 00:09:17.320
And today, we're going to
do it without a grinder.

00:09:17.320 --> 00:09:21.277
